<Time>1618678947464</Time><Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
This was my first time coming to this location. Are usually go to the location on Webster Street but there was a mixup, but everything worked out just fine. It's always hard finding a good vet clinic to take your pets to because you want to feel comfortable and confident since you rely on them to make sure your pet is healthy and in good hands. This is the place to go and BOTH locations are great.

PROS
-Easy appointment booking online or calling.
-Staff is so friendly, patient, understanding and helpful.
-easy drop off appointment due to Covid safety. Just park in the spot, call the front desk and let them know what space number you are in. Easy.
-good location
-Clean office
-They do NOT try to gouge you with unnecessary services or medications. I've had bad experiences with other vet clinics before with my other dog.
-I feel comfortable and always have a peace of mind whenever I take my pet here.
-I have had to book with different veterinarian doctors so I could get the soonest appointment, but they all were great and just all consistently good. :) My last two visits were with Dr. Thurman and she was outstanding. Very thorough and patient when explaining things I wasn't sure about.</text>

<name>RE Casper< /name><time>1548233071982</time><Rating>5< /Rating><Text>This recognition is long time past due, but no less true today than it was when we first walked through the door.‚Ä®‚Ä® In short‚Ä¶ knowledgable, capable, kind, caring and compassionate could all be used to describe this place in our experience.

Long form‚Ä¶ In 2012, our family moved here from the midwest and we are quite fond of our family furball. But, being a full on terrier, he's never without a daredevilish bump or bruise now and then. These things considered, finding a family vet was of high priority.

Fortunately we landed in Alameda when we made the leap out here, and discovered Dr. Wooley at Providence. A meeting that lead to a life saving event for our dog.

He had an episode late one night and we took him in to get checked out at the VCA Emergency Vet down in San Leandro (24hrs and very good as well). While there, they took some biopsies and, well, he tested positive for cancer in a spot on his neck.

We went through the process with VCA... got the diagnosis, treatment options, prices, stomach churning budget realities, hard discussions, tears, the works... Around that time, during a check-up with Dr. Wooley, she stepped in and offered to conduct the procedure herself and in doing so, proved spectacular. The bad bits were removed and the follow-ups were all negative. He was 9 at the time... As of this writing, he is 11yrs young and still dashing around the house with sporadic bursts of terrier energy.

He's got wear on his tires, of course, but no matter what, his life was saved that summer and every new year we have with him is a year given to us by Dr. Wooley and Providence Vet.

We like to think our little dude is equally as appreciative, as any time we walk near the place, he pulls us toward the door, begging to get in. Sometimes I think he's more excited to go to the vet, than he is to go home.

Our deepest thanks and highest recommendation.< /Text>< Pictures>

Up until today this was our fur family's vet, for over 15 years, well I took our cat this Saturday because he had blood in his stool, the doctor examined him then recommended getting some blood work, and the technician would bring an estimate in, she did it was high, so I told her I would do the blood work which was about 345.00, but not the other procedure which was 90, then the doctor came back in and says to his understanding we didn't want to do anything, so I explained that was not what I said, so he crossed off the 90.00 procedure off the pre treatment form and thought that was that, they took my cat back for blood work and than I paid my bill and was told they would call when they get the results back. I got home and noticed they charged me additional 60.00 then discussd, then noticed I had a missed call from them and assumed it was about the overcharge they made but at this point they were closed so today Monday I called and to my surprise they said I needed to pay an additional $30.00, I tried to explain to the lady
what happened but I felt dismissed and not heard, so I told her at our follow up appointment for our dog in a few days we would pay, but changed my mind I wanted to see what pre treatment form I supposedly signed. I got there and I told the lady why I was there and can I please see the pre-treament agreement, she showed me my receipt from my care credit card, they lied to me tried to make me feel like I was wrong, never apologetic or sorry at all, and they did an unauthorized procedure on my cat, so i I told the rude lady I would like copies of my pets records I felt like she was happy to see us go. RUDE ANS SO UNPROFESSIONAL!!!!!!< /Text>

<name>Lisa Tharp<//name>< Review>
We have been bringing our pets to Providence Vet Hospital for several years now.  We had been looking for a new veterinarian for our doxie and our cat for quite some time.  We absolutely love Dr. Woolley!  She is so patient, kind and extremely calm.  Our doxie is almost 10 years old and under Dr. Woolley's care, he has flourished.  He now weighs what he should and we have his seizures under control through proper medication.  We also brought our geriatric cat in to see Dr. Randall Miller and he was just as nice and thorough.  When it came time to decide we had to put our cat down, the entire staff was caring, kind and very thoughtful at a very difficult time for us. The facility is clean and the staff are knowledgeable and professional.  Its is also fairly easy to get appointments with short notice.  I would recommend Providence to anyone who loves their pet and wants them to have the best care!<//Review>

< text>
Laid back atmosphere with friendly staff, delicious beer, and a wide variety of patrons.
They have beer on tap (available both as 4-pour flights and pints) and canned. Wide variety of music keeps the atmosphere upbeat yet cozy. Board games and Mrs. Pacman attract attention of kids and adults alike. Dog friendly and have no problem with you bringing food in.</text>

<Text>A large group of us attending the opening weekend.  We planned to stay for 2 hours.  We ended up having so much fun and stayed for 4 hours.  The beer was so refreshing and delicious. I enjoyed it so much I brought a six pack home with me. I also purchased a limited edition red tee shirt. I got to meet one of the owners. Dennis was super down to earth. Fun Fact:  Dennis mentioned the cool art work was designed by a co-owner. The rest of the employees were so nice and prompt with their service.  At one point the line was out the door but the line moved pretty past. This brewery is kid and pet friendly.  We were offered candy and mixed nuts.  I have ever attended any brewery that offers free snacks.  Looking forward to our next visit.<//Text>< Pics>

<GmapID>0x808fec673da86d05:0xd012bc0aa28d960b<//GmapID><rating>5</rating>< Review>
Cute park. New playground equipment installed early in 2020 (lots of spinny options, still has the ever-popular tire swing, and some great find-the-animal elements for younger kids). Park has now re-opened, with masks and other precautions. We have been to the park several times since reopening. The equipment is well set up for social distancing. Our 3yo daughter loves it.

We also enjoy the walking path around the field, running in the volleyball sand pit (no net for now), and admiring the cairn and mosaic arch. It's a beautiful, well-kept park.<//Review>

< text>
We came to this location at 10:20pm, the location advertises its hours online as 9am-11pm. When we got to the store the doors were locked and the staff inside were ignoring us until we knocked on their door, then the lady with orange curly hair moulthed "closed" to us and when we showed her our phones saying their site says they close at 11pm the lady simply gave us a incredibly rude and condescending thumbs up, we drove from Burbank to Pasadena immediately after work to try and make it in time to buy two exact costumes, because of her lack of customer service we will never be shopping spirit again.</text>

< Review>
I called Yates & Co to help me purchase a custom Lashbrook men's wedding ring.

They were great to work with and were able to give me the best price I could find, and I shopped around a bit before purchasing.

In production my ring ran into an issue.  They were not able to set my inlet gem stone into the standard weight gold.  They upgraded me to the premium weight to make it work (with no cost to me).

When the ring was shipped out to me there was a handwritten note and complementary silicone ring to accompany it.

Working with Yates & Co was an absolute treat.<//Review>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
I'll start by saying, I NEVER give reviews, because I feel like I'm usually satisfied with purchases, but don't feel like singing from the top of a mountain. But my experience with Titanium Jewelry/Yates & Co Jewelers has been more than mountain-shouting worthy. I sincerely appreciate the time and attention given to me as a customer. First, the ring I ordered is absolutely beautiful and unique-I love that my fiance loves it, and the titanium band won't bend or disfigure when he wears it daily on the job. Second, customer service here is outstanding. Working in CS for my entire career, I know that reps really have the opportunity to turn tough situations into wonderful experiences. I believe Yates & Co. really strives to do so. 1. I input an incorrect shipping address for the ring...not an issue, easily updated via email with follow-up from the company. 2. Since I had moved, my credit card billing address was not updated yet. They followed up to make sure that my order processed okay and that they had the correct information on their end. 3. I couldn't figure out where to put my discount code-this upset me, because our budget was tight. I spoke with Amanda on the phone who was so very friendly, helpful, and reassuring. She was able to apply code by working with the orders team. I am very pleased with our order, their great customer service, and I look forward to doing business with them sometime in the future! I thoroughly appreciate a company that has a wonderful physical presence AND online presence. P.S. props to your website designer, media coordinator-the website is so easily navigated.< /review>

< text>
Always enjoy going here.  When my husband and I got engaged I told him the only place he was allowed to purchase our wedding rings was at Yates.  When he ordered the wrong size Titanium wedding band for himself, they exchanged it at no extra charge.  Why is this a big deal?  These rings can not be re-sized once they are made.

Another reason I enjoy shopping at this store, they have unique items.  Yes they do have some standard pieces, like diamond studs.  However, they had a necklace, that if I could have afforded it I would have bought it.  It was a piece of turquoise inside a pearl.  Parts of the pearl were cut away so you could see the turquoise.  It was beautiful.  I haven't seen anything like it anywhere else.

Needless to say I don't shop the cookie cutter jewelry stores that offer inferior jewelry for "financing".  I shop Yates and only Yates.<//text>

1520323451680<//date>
</record></dataset><record>
<Resp>None<//Resp>< text>
Really excellent tea! Tried the pu-erh and one of the oolongs, and managed to milk the pu-erh through several steepings. The folks there source their teas directly, from what I understand, and make a couple of their own blends, and they REALLY know their stuff. Also got one each of the buns and a rice ball, and two mochi. I was there with a group, and you order up front, take your snacks or mochi to your table, and they bring you any of the cooked food and tea. Everything was brought quite promptly.

It's a fairly quiet place, but nobody seemed to mind us chattering away at a low volume. A number of folk were at small tables reading or working on laptops, and each table has its own electric kettle. Very civilized. It felt like a great place to come with a book or maybe a casual date.

My 5yo was part of our group, and the folks who run the place treated her with great aplomb, helping her pick from the small snack choices they had on offer and giving her a tasting cup for her tea. I was really happy with how courteous they were to her, given her age, but I guess they could tell she was on her best manners. I'm looking forward to coming back with her and my sweetie sometime!</text>

<Resp>None<//Resp>< text>
This is the spot for a grounded, Zen, pure experience of Tea.

I have not been to other tearooms in SF yet, mostly because from my google searches, it seems that a lot of them are more "trendy" or are culturally based in English High Noon fancy frills tea service (nothing wrong with them, but to me, Tea is an eastern thing). Atmosphere is spaciously intimate, music is subtle, but complimentary (Pandora did a stellar job with their jazz playlist today, mmm Ben Webster). The owner is lovely, and the entire place constantly reminds you "be here now."< /text>

<Time>1483568393333</Time><Rate>5</Rate>< review>
Calm and spacious. I love sitting here with a pot of pu erh. They have a great selection, and everyone I have talked to here has a good knowledge of their teas. Today I ordered the Ochazuke, and it was exactly what I craved. They use a fancier tea than I would use (sencha/ matcha rather than genmaicha), so the flavor of the tea was more pronounced than usual. I loved that they later offered pickled plum. A perfect spot for a rainy day.<//review>

109026571278474805170< /user>

< text>
I'm partial to oolongs and greens and good quality oolongs are fairly rare in my area. I'm willing to drive 50' to get here.
Their Alishan is divine but overpriced if you compare it to Pasadena's Bird Pick: $50 for 4.75oz whereas Bird Pick (and others, in SF) sell 4oz of a very similar quality for $30.
Dong Ding is, for me, the best value: comforting warm and floral aroma, leaves are whole, very few twigs, it steeps quite comfortably 5 times, 4.75oz - $30.
Green Goddess has a beautiful emerald green color but the leaves (after steeping) look broken, with many twigs, the 3rd steeping is already pushing it in terms of flavor which is slightly grassier and more simplistic than Dong Ding.
Osmanthus oolong is good but not as good as Bird Pick's Osmanthus Milk Oolong.
Their Sencha is inferior.
I'd rather not drive all the way to San Francisco from the South Bay, so that's the best oolong I can find along the way.
I also enjoyed having a tea inside. However a different table other than next to the window would have been too dark for me; I like to see the color of my tea and leaves...<//text>

3<//rating>

< username>
Peter Xaymountry</username>
< Time>
1601173405173< /Time>
<rate>5<//rate>< text>
I stopped by here yesterday because it's near my office and I wanted to check this place out for a while. I was looking to get some water spots remover and instead of relying on Amazon I figure I could just get it today. They have a very small parking lot that is shared with a auto shop so be aware of that. If you drive a truck, it would be better for you to park on street. When I walked in, the staff was very friendly and asked if I needed any help. They took me to where the water spot remover is, so I was just looking around afterwards. They have mostly Chemical Guys product so if you're there for that brand then you'll find what you want.</text>

< Review>
I contemplated posing this review but the mistreatment of guests by the manager on duty at Cheesecake factory Stoneridge mall, Pleasanton, Ca location needs to be called out so other patrons of this establishment are made aware of their deceptive practices, miscommunication, blatant lies, lack of training and disrespecting their guests and complete unprofessional and demeanor.

We went to have early lunch to celebrate a special occasion but the terrible experience at the restaurant ruined it completely for us. We ordered their lunch special that comes with a slice of cheesecake. Later, we were humiliated by the manager on duty .... and the server in front of other patrons who were eating on the outside patio around us. When placing the order we "specifically" mentioned to the server  that "we would like to order this lunch special that comes with a slice of cheesecake. This was the first opportunity for the server to let us know that it was for online orders only, which she obviously did not do. Then, we asked if we needed to let her know the type of cheesecake and order it with the food or can we order it later? This was opportunity #2: Ther server .... said, "no, you don't have to let me know now. You can order the slice later. BOTH times the server had the opportunity to let us know that it was part of an online special and couldn't be ordered.

While we were having our meal, the servers were switched, as the one who took our order had finished her shift. Once we finished eating our meal, we asked the new server  for the cheesecake that was part of the lunch special. She went inside, came back and informed us that it was not offered with our meal. We asked her why and she said her manager said so. We asked to speak to the manager. The manager came out after 10-15 minutes and was adamant about the lunch special not inclusive of cheesecake. He was extremely arrogant, cocky and down right rude with no inkling of customer service. It was evident that he had no tack or training to handle guest service issues. He lacked basic guest resolution knowledge and training. He then called the server who took our order, put his arms around her and said loudly, ".... , did you tell these guests that their lunch special came with cheesecake" which all the guests on the patio could hear.  It was humiliating  and demeaning.  Is it allowed for male managers to put their arms around female workers? Where is HR?

The entire experience for us to celebrate a milestone for our kid was ruined by the staff and manager  SAMMY GONSALVES who was rude, disrespectful and downright arrogant and had no class or qualification to be a manager on duty let  alone  talk to guests.

We contacted guest care and they kind of just threw their hands in the air and gave us the "canned speech" of what they are trained to do and the same generic verbiage to every customer. We asked to receive a call from the general manager of the restaurant who never called us back for several weeks, despite sending reminder emails to their customer care team. After a few weeks we called guest care again and they probably asked the GM to call us. When the GM called us her entire tone & demeanor was like it was a huge inconvenience for her to give us a call. She was equally rude, nonchalant and arrogant in her approach so we simply ended the conversation. It is evident that the culture of the entire CKF Pleasanton is "don't care" and guests are not important since they are always so busy, do a lot of business so they essentially don't have to worry about whether or not their guests have a good experience. THS IS UNACCEPTABLE AS WE HAVE PATRONIZED THE CHEESECAKE FACTORY SINCE 1996 IN ALL 3 STATES THAT WE HAVE LIVED IN. Furthermore, guests' experience in their restaurants and how they are treated by the staff there is also not important to CKF customer service and even to their higher management, as it is evident in the way they handled our terrible experience and how we were treated by their manager. I WILL NEVER EAT HERE AGAIN !!!!!!!!!!<//Review>

Review for online ordering system:
1. website easy to navigate

2. The pickup time is an ESTIMATE only. My order was requested for 11:45, got a TEXT around 12:30 that my order was ready , luckily I had errands to do in the area otherwise I would be annoyed haha.

3. arrived at curbside check in spot, texted in my spot number and they came out and brought my order

4. They did forget my cheesecake, that's the whole reason I did the order!  but luckily I checked before I left, so the staff person brought that out after.

PASTA DA VINCI: asked for extra mushrooms and sauce in order, def got extra sauce, don't think I got extra mushrooms

< review>
Amazing food and great service. But be ready for wait time of 60-90 minutes.

If they could just create a better system for booking the overall experience would be amazing.

Current scenarios (personally experienced so many times)
- wait period to get to table is 30-60 minutes
- wait period for the server to come 10-15 minutes
- wait period for food to be served is 30-45.

By the time you get to food you are tired of waiting.

Why can‚Äôt we:
- have an online system for booking a table? Saves 30-60 minutes of customer to wait in the restaurant with a buzzer in hand.
- online system for food preference so that kitchen starts preparing as soon as you sit on table. Save server interaction time.<//review>

< Review>
Checked in for a party of five at 7:40 pm. Was told wait would be an hour and 15 minutes. Ladies at front were on their phones. One was sick and was wiping her nose on her shirt.  Didn't get seated until 9:30. Waitress was bothered for some reason. Bad service. The waitress knew we waited along time. She vented about people complaining. Took forever to get our drinks. My daughter still didn't have her drink so we had to ask waitress. Sat near kitchen and could see food sitting for 15+ minutes. Finally brought some of our food. My youngest son went to take his plate and it spilt all over him. Hot fries all in his lap. Who hands an 11 year old a hot plate? Why don't they set it down for you? Then our older sons food was "taken" by someone else. The waitress said it would be another 10+ minutes for his food to come out. So he had to watch us eat.  Husband's food came minus the fried onions...had to wait on those to come out. No ketchup on table..only four sets of silverware and we were five people. We were being kind to the waitress, it wasn't her fault we waited so long. But her service was bad, had to flag her down for refill, straws, ketchup etc. We sat and waited,  finally got our bill. She brought boxes for leftovers. But left our empty plates and cups sitting. Never cleared the table. What a horrible experience. You think after all the things that went wrong, the spilling food on our child, my son waiting for his food to arrive, while we ate,  that she'd comp a meal, or offer a dessert. Nothing. The bill was $110 and some change. I put in $111.00 and she didn't return our change. Returned with a receipt to sign....still never cleared the table. All in all we were there for three hours. Left close to 11 pm.. pretty terrible. We visited last year around this time and had a wonderful experience. This time was quite opposite and I don't think we will return. Drove out here from San Joaquin County....and what a joke tonight was.</Review>

On Cyber Monday, The Cheesecake Factory ran a promotion on Instagram that was too good to pass up--buy a $25 gift card and you get 2 free slices of cheesecake (or layer cake for that matter).  Naturally, I bought the $25 gift for us! :) I love their cheesecakes here, so it was a no brainer.

We went a few weeks ago to redeem one of the free desserts and use our gift card. We got there during HH, so I got their HH Margarita. It was a good price at $6. It was too sweet for me though, so I will definitely not order that again. I'll stick to the wine next time.

I ordered the Chicken Bellagio which was pretty good. It came with basil pasta, thinly sliced chicken breast that's been breaded and fried, some greens, and prosciutto on top. It's a huge portion as most of their entrees tend to be, so I ate half and brought the other half home so I can have some dessert. The hubby ordered the Steak Diane with Mashed Potatoes. It was quite good. The beef was tender and tasty. The portion was just right for him too.

I was craving Chocolate Cake so we decided to forgo the cheesecake and get the Black Out Cake. I was disappointed that the cake was served cold. It should have been served at room temperature. We ate a couple of bites of it and took the rest home. I left it on our kitchen counter overnight and we had it the next day with coffee and it was much better. It's still a little sweeter than I prefer. I really wish TCF would tone down the sweetness of their drinks and desserts.

I have one more free cheesecake to redeem, so we'll be back during HH and get the HH Burger which we've had before and is actually a good burger.<//Review>< UserId.>

<Rating>4< /Rating>< review>
The cheesecake factory is an interesting place to eat. I mean that in a good way. It has a wide variety of foods from tamales to cheeseburgers. It's delicious. It can make you like foods that you've never even heard of before. The staff are also very friendly. Once they accidentally burnt a pie crust for a Shepard's Pie. They took the situation very kindly by creating another one right away and giving it to me for free. They even offered me a free soup and drink! They are also popular for their cheesecakes if you've haven't noticed. They have a great assortment of cheesecakes from The Original and an Oreo Cheesecake. It all tastes splendid. The only reason why I'm giving it 4 stars is because the wait for me personally is way too long and it's too dark at the night. The atmosphere is very enjoyable and unique but you can barely see it let alone the menu.<//review>

<Review>It is really upsetting for me to rate my all time fav place this low. However the food and service we recieved yesterday at the Pleasanton cheesecake factory calls for a low rating. We went there for a celebratory dinner and ordered our usual dishes.... thai lettuce wrap for me and shrimp scampi.
The food came after a long long wait. Which is not an issue considering the place was very crowded. However when the dishes came we noticed that the pasta was lumpy... and not just 1 lump in a plateful of pasta but a lot of lumps.
So we called the server over and asked her if the dish could be re- made. Which in itself was a process since she seemed really busy. Our dishes had been brought over by someone else. While we waited for the pasta to be remade we started working on the thai lettuce wraps. We noticed that some of the leaves had mud splatters which was quite shocking since this dish is only assembling salad ingredients on a platter... one would assume that the ingredients would be cleaned before sending a dish out.
When the chef came over with the corrected pasta dish we showed him the mud splattered lettuce and he offered to replace the dish. Needless to say by this time our night was quite spoilt and we requested for the food to be packed to go.
Attached are the pics showing after so many mess ups cheesecake factory messed up packing the dish. A container of sauce was open and and upended on the lettuce. A godiva cheesecake package did not have the chocolate piece unwrapped and on the cheesecake as expected but instead was just dumped in the package.

< Review>
My wife and I had dinner here on Saturday night. We got the chicken taquitos to start and we both agreed they were fantastic. Great flavors, well cooked, with a great salsa and avocado sauce.  I got the Hamachi steak and my wife got the Vegan Cobb salad. My steak was perfection! I was really surprised at the tenderness of the meat and quality of the cut. The cook on it was also exactly medium rare. Maybe a little under, but that's better than overcooked. The tempura asparagus was not very good. Very fried tasting and not my favorite. The wasabi mashed potatoes were okay, just a little too cold, but the taste was fine. Again, the steak was amazing. My wife loved her salad and said she would order it again. The wine pours were great as well. Great service at the bar while waiting and the server was on top of everything at all times. We will be back!<//Review>

<Text>My wife was blessed enough to receive a gift certificate to use as she pleased at the Cheesecake Factory restaurant. It was our first visit there. Right off the bat the customer service is excellent. Soon as we walked in the door we were greeted with a smile even though it was busy. If they were stressed out you wouldn't know it which is good nowadays they have that kind of customer service. The reason why we gave this place 4 stars was because the Bland tasting crust on the Fish & Chip order. The fish inside was cooked perfectly but the batter for the cod was tasteless. The correct amount of seasonings should fix this matter easily. Presentation was beautiful and the appetizers were cook perfectly. Two people can eat off the fish and chip order by the way . Another reason for the 4 stars was that we felt that the music was a tad bit loud. Very difficult to tell your order to the waiter when you can barely hear him or yourself over the music and the crowd noise. Maybe the volume needs to be adjusted when it gets too busy? I forgot to mention that when I did say something about the cod being bland, the waiter was more than willing to fix the situation without making me feel guilty about it :-)
My wife just found the receipt. The waiter name is Kevin Güòä

Our table, had place settings for four but "everyone's" silverware had "dried on food stains" on them. ¬†Our table "still had food particles left" from the previous diners. ¬†Is it too much to request that tables are prepared properly for the next customers?

Awful. We have made a few attempts to give this location the benefit of the doubt. We have yet to have a pleasant experience here. There is generally a fairly long wait (even on a Tuesday night), and the food takes absolutely forever to make it to the table. Half the time some item is not available because they are "out" or it's poorly made (typically way over cooked). Our recent trip being no exception, we even got the added benefit of super hot children's plates with hot fries that the server spilled all over my son because she couldn't reach across the table. Waited almost half an hour for my burnt chicken sandwich to be re-made, and it only took what should have been our entire meal time to get luke warm, way over-salted fries for the adult entrees. This was after the manager (whom we did not request to speak to BECAUSE they do nothing) stopped by our table to check on us. It has never taken less than 1h 20min+ from the time we are seated, which is crazy because we usually know our order upon sitting down having waited forever just to get in. Lord help you if you need a refill on your drink. Drive a little further and go to the Walnut Creek location, having to pay for parking and the added distance is worth it to not have to go through this. I'm a reasonable person. I understand if a restaurant is busy, and we don't make special requests, we are polite to our servers and don't let our kids make a mess. This location is just so poorly run. Needless to say, we won't be back.<//text>

Once the steaks came out, the husbands noticed that it didn't have any glaze or any sauce on the steak and the meat was extremely dry and tough. They called the waitress over and she called the manager. When he came over, he took the plates away and said they would make new ones. After waiting another 20 minutes, by this time, were were all anxious to leave, the manager came back and said they never had the hibachi steak, what they had provided to us was a different type of steak that they tried to make look like hibachi, these are his words not ours. Cheesecakes are always good over here. Ambience is fine. I generally like the food. I have tried multiple items over here, but they are mostly on the expensive side. Among all the times I have visited this restaurant (at this location) I've always had mixed reaction about the attendants at the reception and the servers.
I've visited this location multiple times. On Feb 4, 2018 I took my cousin, who was visiting US, to this place. We gave him really great hopes about the restaurant but it turned out to be a massive disappointment. We were seated after a wait of 30 minutes - which I do not mind at all. Once seated we kept waiting for more than 15 minutes just for a server to show up and offer us water, etc. It was totally unacceptable. Someone showed up only after we left the chair to find a server. After we placed the ordered the food arrived after some time. I wouldn't say that it took a lot of time for the food to arrive but it wasn't quick.
Anyway, the food was good. We had ordered some cocktails, Cajun Jambalaya, Shrimp Dynamite and Thai Lettuce Wrap (veggy - chicken replaced with avocado). Later on we found that there was a mess up in the bill. We told the server and she corrected and brought it back to us. But we found that there was the same as before - we again had to find her to fix it.
My last experience wasn't great at all and especially a poor 1st impression for my cousin on Cheesecake Factory!!!<//Text>

<Text>Mixed success on food, but SUPER SLOW!

We just went here for lunch.  My grandkids have to eat gluten free and the 4 year old is excessively difficult to feed.  It took over a half an hour for our order to be taken and then more than 30 minutes for our food.  With a wild 4 year old, this was a ridiculous amount of time.  It was lunch time on a Saturday, so we expected busy, but it was an hour wait to eat inside(which does not factor into this review), so we sat outside.  We heard our waiter comment that waiters are supposed to be assigned only 4 tables, but he had 7, so, clearly, they were understaffed.  At one point, he apologized that the food order was taking so long and said it would be out in "a few minutes." nearly 20 minutes later, our food arrived.  First half our party's meals and then, 5 minutes later, the other half.
My grand daughter's gluten free pasta(Carbonara) was super oily and lacking in flavor and was cooked to varying degrees--some cooked decently, but about half still hard.  Gluten free pasta is not difficult to cook, btw--for the most part, it's just like plain pasta.  My youngest daughter's turkey burger came out not as ordered(no onions) and the patty was hard; the sweet potato fries cold.
My Jambalaya pasta with brown rice was really good.  My older daughter liked her garlic noodles with shrimp(had plenty of veggies), but it was pretty oily.  We got cheesecake to go and that was great.
While I really liked the Jambalaya and cheesecake, I recommend coming when it's slow and be careful what you order.< /Text><pictures>None<//pictures><Response>{'time': 1488221365510, 'text': 'Hi Yefim, Thank you for your feedback!
